{
  "doc_id": "41241",
  "text": "Substance with a high atomic number (e.g., iodine and lanthanoids) is used as a contrast agent in X-ray CT [CITATION_1] . The use of such heavy elements yields the undesirable cupping artifact [CITATION_2] , which makes the quantitative CT image analysis difficult. The degree of the cupping depends on the atomic number of the heavy element [CITATION_3] . In this section, we applied the exact solutions obtained in Sec. 2 to the search for the atomic number of the best contrast agent that induces the least cupping artifact.",
